12/12/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The government's Security Council was due to convene on Monday (12 December) to review issues related to the crime rate, preparations for a new bill to fight organised crime, and the draft strategy for integrated border management. The council will also analyse the pace at which high profile criminal cases are processed, a probe that is to be completed by 20 December. (Mediapool, BNR - 12/12/05) 
